crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a MIPS-based IoT botnet, exhibiting characteristic behaviors of the Mirai or Gafgyt malware families. Key malicious indicators include: XOR-based string obfuscation used to hide commands and configuration (sub_40d5b8, sub_40d69c); manual construction of HTTP and raw network headers for various DDoS attack vectors (sub_4049e8, sub_400cac); and a hardcoded C2 infrastructure IP address (20.211.168.70). The binary implements process daemonization via fork/setsid and uses prctl to mask its process name. The presence of Mirai-style attack signatures like 'POST /cdn-cgi/' and specific User-Agent/Cookie handling confirms its role as a DDoS bot.
